        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:52PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Maxton, Antioch, Gibson, East Laurinburg, and Laurel
Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
